---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout title="Terms of Service -- Prompt-Armor" description="Terms of service for Prompt-Armor.">
  <Header />

  <main class="flex-1 max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-armor-white mb-4">Terms of Service</h1>
    <p class="text-xs text-armor-muted mb-8">Last updated: March 14, 2026</p>

    <div class="space-y-8 text-sm text-armor-text leading-relaxed">

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-armor-white mb-3">1. Scope</h2>
        <p class="text-armor-muted">
          These terms of service govern the use of the Prompt-Armor web application
          ("Service") operated by Belkis Aslani ("Operator"). By accessing or using
          the Service, you agree to be bound by these terms.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-armor-white mb-3">2. Description of Service</h2>
        <p class="text-armor-muted">
          Prompt-Armor is a free online tool that encodes AI prompts into tamper-evident
          blocks using Base64 encoding and SHA-256 hashing. All processing happens entirely
          in the user's browser. No data is transmitted to or stored on any server.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-armor-white mb-3">3. Free of charge</h2>
        <p class="text-armor-muted">
          The Service is currently provided <strong class="text-armor-white">free of charge</strong>
          for personal and non-commercial use. The Operator reserves the right to change the
          pricing model in the future with reasonable advance notice.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-armor-white mb-3">4. Commercial use</h2>
        <p class="text-armor-muted">
          Commercial use of the Service, the underlying source code, or the Prompt-Armor method
          requires a separate commercial license. This includes, but is not limited to, selling
          protected prompts, integrating the system into commercial products, or offering the
          Service as part of a paid offering.
        </p>
        <p class="text-armor-muted mt-3">
          For commercial licensing inquiries, please contact:
          <a href="mailto:belkis.aslani@gmail.com" class="text-armor-accent hover:text-armor-accent-hover transition-colors">
            belkis.aslani@gmail.com
          </a>
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-armor-white mb-3">5. No warranty</h2>
        <p class="text-armor-muted">
          The Service is provided "as is" without any warranty, express or implied. The Operator
          does not guarantee that:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-armor-muted mt-2 space-y-1">
          <li>The Service will be available at all times without interruption</li>
          <li>The Service will be free of errors or defects</li>
          <li>AI models will follow the system instructions in the armor block in all cases</li>
          <li>The tamper-detection mechanism provides absolute protection against all forms of modification</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-armor-white mb-3">6. Limitation of liability</h2>
        <p class="text-armor-muted">
          The Operator shall not be liable for any direct, indirect, incidental, special,
          consequential, or exemplary damages arising from the use or inability to use the
          Service, even if the Operator has been advised of the possibility of such damages.
        </p>
        <p class="text-armor-muted mt-3">
          This limitation does not apply to liability for intent or gross negligence, or to
          mandatory liability under applicable law.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-armor-white mb-3">7. Intellectual property</h2>
        <p class="text-armor-muted">
          The Prompt-Armor concept, source code, design, and all associated materials are the
          intellectual property of Belkis Aslani. Use is permitted only within the scope of
          the <a href="https://github.com/BEKO2210/Prompt_Copyrighting/blob/main/LICENSE"
                 class="text-armor-accent hover:text-armor-accent-hover transition-colors">
          Prompt-Armor License</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-armor-white mb-3">8. User responsibility</h2>
        <p class="text-armor-muted">
          You are solely responsible for the content of the prompts you protect using this
          Service. The Operator has no access to and no knowledge of the content you encode.
          You agree not to use the Service for any unlawful purpose or to encode content that
          violates applicable laws.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-armor-white mb-3">9. Changes to the terms</h2>
        <p class="text-armor-muted">
          The Operator reserves the right to modify these terms at any time. Changes will be
          published on this page with an updated date. Continued use of the Service after
          changes constitutes acceptance of the new terms.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-armor-white mb-3">10. Governing law and jurisdiction</h2>
        <p class="text-armor-muted">
          These terms shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the
          Federal Republic of Germany. The courts of Stuttgart, Germany, shall have exclusive
          jurisdiction over any disputes arising from these terms, to the extent permitted by law.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-armor-white mb-3">11. Contact</h2>
        <p class="text-armor-muted">
          For questions about these terms, please contact:
        </p>
        <p class="mt-2">
          Belkis Aslani<br/>
          Vogelsangstr. 32<br/>
          71691 Freiberg am Neckar, Germany<br/>
          Email:
          <a href="mailto:belkis.aslani@gmail.com" class="text-armor-accent hover:text-armor-accent-hover transition-colors">
            belkis.aslani@gmail.com
          </a>
        </p>
      </section>

    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
